11. Limitations of Spring Boot (Interview Honesty)

âŒ Less control due to auto-configuration
âŒ Opinionated defaults may not fit all cases
âŒ Debugging auto-config can be tricky
âŒ Not ideal for extremely low-level frameworks

Good interview answer
â€œSpring Boot trades fine-grained control for developer productivity.â€

12. Common Interview Questions & Answers
Q1. What is Spring Boot?
Spring Boot is a framework that simplifies Spring application development using auto-configuration and embedded servers.

Q2. How does Spring Boot reduce configuration?
By using:
Auto-configuration
Starter dependencies
Convention over configuration

Q3. What is @SpringBootApplication?

Combination of:
@Configuration
@EnableAutoConfiguration
@ComponentScan

Q4. Can we disable auto-configuration?
âœ… Yes
@SpringBootApplication(exclude = DataSourceAutoConfiguration.class)

Q5. Is Spring Boot suitable for large applications?
âœ… Yes â€” widely used in enterprise & microservices

13. Tricky Interview Questions (ğŸ”¥ 4+ Years Level)
â“ Is Spring Boot replacing Spring?
âŒ No
âœ” Spring Boot uses Spring internally

â“ Is Spring Boot only for microservices?
âŒ No
âœ” Can be monolith or microservice

â“ Does Spring Boot require XML?
âŒ No (but can use if needed)

â“ Can we deploy Spring Boot as WAR?
âœ… Yes (but JAR is preferred)

â“ Does Spring Boot remove the need for Spring MVC?
âŒ No
âœ” It configures Spring MVC automatically

â“ How does Spring Boot know what to auto-configure?
âœ” Uses:
